# Nexmarket Cliente — environment

# Google Maps API key (Android/iOS need it for the live delivery-tracking map).
# After setting this, also paste it into app.json:
#   android.config.googleMaps.apiKey  and  ios.config.googleMapsApiKey
EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY="YOUR_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY"

# Google Sign-In client IDs (RF01). Create them in Google Cloud Console and
# paste into app.json > extra.googleAuth. They are public client IDs (safe to
# ship), not secrets.
#   expoClientId / iosClientId / androidClientId / webClientId

# The Firebase project is SHARED with the loja and entregador apps and lives in
# firebase-config.json (committed on purpose, mirroring the other repos).
# No Firebase secrets are needed here for client usage.

# Payments: card data is tokenized directly by the PSP SDK (Stripe / MercadoPago
# / Pagar.me). Put the PSP *publishable* key in the native build config when you
# wire src/lib/payments.ts to a real provider — never store secret keys in the app.
